    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Sections show renal tissue cores revealing tubular dilatation with necrosis of epithelial cells. Some peritubular chronic inflammatory cells are seen.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>AdenoCA Prostate_needle biopsy</title>
    <created>20171226T081917Z</created>
    <updated>20260425T020138Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS: </div><div>Prostate, right left, TRUS-guided biopsy --- Acinar adenocarcinoma (with Gleason score _ + _ = _).</div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:</div><div>Received are _ pieces of tissue measuring up to _ x 0.1 x 0.1 cm.</div><div><br/></div><div>All for section and labeled as _A _B.</div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC DESCRIPTION:</div><div>Tumor histological type: Acinar adenocarcinoma</div><div>Tumor histological grade:</div><div>_ Grade group 1 (Gleason Score 3 + 3 = 6) </div><div>_ Grade group 2 (Gleason Score 3 + 4 = 7) </div><div style="padding-left:40px;"><b><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Percentage of Pattern 4:  _ </span></b><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Less than or equal to 5%_ 6 - 10%_ 11 - 20%_ 21 - 30%_ 31 - 40%_ Greater than 40%</span></div><div>_ Grade group 3 (Gleason Score 4 + 3 = 7) </div><div style="padding-left:40px;">Percentage of Pattern 4:___ Less than 61% ___ 61 - 70% ___ 71 - 80% __ 81 - 90% ___ Greater than 90%</div><div>_ Grade group 4 (Gleason Score 4 + 4 = 8) </div><div>_ Grade group 4 (Gleason Score 3 + 5 = 8) </div><div>_ Grade group 4 (Gleason Score 5 + 3 = 8) </div><div>_ Grade group 5 (Gleason Score 4 + 5 = 9) </div><div>_ Grade group 5 (Gleason Score 5 + 4 = 9) </div><div>_ Grade group 5 (Gleason Score 5 + 5 = 10)</div><div>Tumor volume:</div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">- Number cores positive: _ </span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">- Total number of cores: _    </span></div><div>- Greatest percentage of core involvement by cancer in any core<span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">: _%</span></div><div>Intraductal Carcinoma (IDC): _Present / Not identified </div><div>- IDC Incorporated into Grade:___ Yes/___ No</div><div>Cribriform glands: Not identified___ Present</div><div>Lymphovascular invasion: _Not identified</div><div>Perineural invasion: _Not identified
<b><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Periprostatic Fat Invasion:</span></b><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ Not identified ___ Present</span></div><div>Immunohistochemical studies: No basal cells surrounding the neoplastic glands are demonstrated by p63 and 34betaE12. The neoplastic glands are positive for AMACR, confirming the diagnosis.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>(This case has been reviewed by two pathologists.)</div><div><br/></div><hr/><div>Reference:</div><div>1.Well differentiation (Gleason sun, 6 or less); moderate (7); poor (8-10)</div><div>2.Simple definitions for Gleason grade:</div><div>Grade 1: Well-circumscribed nodule of adenocarcinoma composed of crowded well-differentiated glands;</div><div>Grade 2: Similar to pattern 1 but with minor infiltration at border;</div><div>Grade 3: Well-formed glands infiltrating benign glands;</div><div>Grade 4: Fused poorly-defined glands, large cribriform glands, hypernephroid pattern;</div><div>Grade 5: Undifferentiated masses or single cells</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>AML, angiomyolipoma</title>
    <created>20160818T053559Z</created>
    <updated>20160818T053604Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><div><span style="color: rgb(153, 51, 0); font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif;"><br clear="none" /></span></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif;">The tissue fragments are composed predominantly of mature adipose tissue along with spindled and epithelioid myoid cells, and thick-walled blood vessels. Mitotic activity is rare (&lt;1/10 HPF). Fat necrosis with aggregates of foamy histiocytes, and hemorrhage are seen in focal areas.</span></div><br clear="none" /></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
