  <note>
    <title>chronic inflammation p53, CK20  [CI_IHC]</title>
    <created>20200523T064201Z</created>
    <updated>20200523T064223Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.mac</source>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>The urinary bladder mucosa showed denuded urothelium in which the maturation cannot be well appreciated. p53 and CK20 were performed to assist the exlusion of urothelial carcinoma in situ. Some denuded urothelial cells mimicked nephrogenic metaplasia.  Pax8 was performed and arguring against nephrogenic metaplasia. <br/></div><div> </div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Confirmed, vas deferens, bilateral, vasectomy [vas]</title>
