  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Consistent with median raphe cyst (penis)</title>
    <created>20170117T010405Z</created>
    <updated>20240923T053642Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>consistent with median raphe cyst.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description: </div><div>Section shows a cystic tissue lined by stratified epithelium with occasional mucous  cells. The epithelium is focally ulcerated accompanied by mixed inflammatory  infiltrate and capillary proliferation in the underlying stroma. Accumulation of  histiocytes are also seen. No Treponema pallidum microorganisms are demonstrated by  Warthin-Starry stain. No fungus is highlighted by GMS and PAS.  No adjacent penis epithelium is identified. No malignancy is observed. </div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
