<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>non-invasive papillary urothelial carcinoma, with mixed low- and high-grade areas (pTa).</div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC DESCRIPTION:</div><div>1. Histologic type: non-invasive papillary urothelial</div><div>   carcinoma, with mixed low- and high-grade areas.</div><div>2. Histologic grade: low-grade (_%) and high-grade (_%)</div><div>3. Extent of invasion: pTa: Papillary noninvasive carcinoma</div><div>4. Urothelial carcinoma in situ: present  absent</div><div>5. Peritumoral lymphovascular invasion: Absent</div><div>6. Perineural invasion: Absent</div><div>7. Margin:</div><div>Tumor base: Presence of tumor element,   with/   without finding of muscular invasion</div><div>9. Muscularis propria presence: Present Absent</div><div>10. Lymph nodes: Not assessed</div><div>11. pTNM: pTaNx (AJCC cancer staging system, 8th edition)</div><div>12. TNM descriptors: Not applicable.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
