  <note>
    <title>Non-invasive papillary UC</title>
    <created>20170222T081029Z</created>
    <updated>20250213T043033Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>non-invasive papillary urothelial carcinoma, high-grade</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows fibroepithelial tissue lined by urothelial cells with focal papillary structures, featuring high-grade nuclear feature, and loss of polarity. No stromal invasion is seen.</div><div>Section shows papillary fronds lined by urothelial cells with loss of polarity and nuclear pleomorphism. The backgroud shows mixed inflammatory infiltrate.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20190102T044920Z</created>
    <updated>20190403T065824Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>non-invasive papillary urothelial carcinoma, with mixed low- and high-grade areas.</div><div><br/></div><div>Section shows fibrovascular cores lined by urothelial cells</div><div>of variable thickness. It is composed of low- and high-grade</div><div>areas; the latter accounts for around 15%, in which</div><div>disordered architecture and cytological atypia are seen.</div><div>No stromal invasion is seen in this specimen.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
