  <note>
    <title>Oncocytoma</title>
    <created>20161011T085255Z</created>
    <updated>20161011T131218Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <source>mobile.android</source>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note>
<div><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; float: none; display: inline !important;">Sections show a well-demarcated tumor composed of solid nests of tumor cells in a hyalinized stroma. The tumor cells are uniform with polygonal shape, featuring eosinophilic and granular cytoplasm, and uniform round nuclei. Immunohistochemically, the tumor cells are diffusely positive for CD117, focally positive for CD10 but not S-100. Hale colloidal iron stain is negative. </span></span></div>
<div><span style="font-size: 38.2327px;"><span style="font-family: Arial;"><br/></span></span></div>
</en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Oncocytoma (with degenerative atypia)</title>
    <created>20170221T151338Z</created>
    <updated>20170221T151350Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.mac</source>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="color: rgb(43, 43, 43); font-family: Lato, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(248, 250, 245); float: none;">The tumor is composed of cells with abundant eosinophilic cytoplasm. Focally, cells are arranged in nests in a fibromyxoid stroma. In this area the well-preserved nuclei that with fine chromatin are uniformly round with variably sized nucleoli. However, the majority of cells have prominent atypia, yet the atypia appears degenerative nuclear atypia with multinucleation, pseudoinclusions, and indistinct smudgy chromatin. Mitotic figures and necrosis are absent.</span><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Papillary RCC</title>
    <created>20170221T151125Z</created>
    <updated>20170221T151148Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.mac</source>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><font style="font-size: 12px;" face="Gulim"><span style="color: rgb(43, 43, 43); font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(248, 250, 245); float: none;"><span style="color: rgb(43, 43, 43); font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(248, 250, 245); float: none;"> The tumor is composed of large, round to polygonal cells with abundant e</span>osinophilic cytoplasm. Architecturally, there are numerous papillary fronds lined by multilayered columnar granular eosinophilic/oncocytic cells. The nuclei are relatively round with prominent nucleoli. Numerous foamy histiocytes occupy the papillary fibrovascular cores. Hemosiderin deposition is present in some of the histiocytes as well in some of the epithelium.</span><br/></font></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Pheochromocytoma</title>
    <created>20170216T065534Z</created>
    <updated>20221028T053430Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><div>Pheochromocytoma</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Section shows adrenal gland tissue with a tumor composed of uniform oval cells arranged in organoid pattern with interspersed small blood vessels.</div><div>and being positive for synaptophysin ///. No necrosis is noted. Mitosis is</div><div>hardly identified. The sustentacular cells are highlighted by S-100.  </div><div><br/></div><div> Life-long follow-up is recommended.</div><div><br/></div><hr/><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Histological tumor type: Pheochromocytoma</div><div>Tumor dimensions: _ cm. (pT1: &lt;5 cm in greatest</div><div>  dimension, no extra-adrenal invasion)</div><div>Extent of invasion: Confined within adrenal gland</div><div>Lymphovascular invasion: Absent</div><div>Margin status: Free, _ mm in distance.</div><div>Proliferative fraction :</div><div>  Mitoses: &lt;1/10 high-power fields</div><div>  Ki-67: 10% (hot spot)</div><div>Lymph node status: Not assessed</div><div>Immunohistochemical stains:</div><div>  Synaptophysin: positive</div><div>  Chromogranin A: positive</div><div>  Inhibin: focally positive</div><div>  Melan-A: negative</div><div>  S100: The sustentacular cells are highlighted by S-100.</div><div>pTNM: pT1 (AJCC cancer staging system, 8th edition).</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>GAPP Risk Stratification: low/Intermediate/high</div><div>  Histological Pattern: </div><div>  Cellularity: )</div><div>  Comedo necrosis: </div><div>  Vascular/ Capsular invasion: </div><div>  Ki-67 labelling index: </div><div>  Catecholamine phenotypes: </div><div>  Maximum Total Score: </div><div>  Grading: </div><div>  Risk Stratification: </div><div><br/></div><div>NOTE: The GAPP Histological Algorithm should be used as rule-out algorithm, and is best interpreted in</div><div>conjunction with clinical and molecular data.</div><hr/><div><br/></div></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
