<div style="padding-left: 30px;"><br clear="none" /></div>
<p><span style="font-family: 'times new roman', times, serif;">Basal cells surrounding the glands are highlighted by <span style="color: #ff6600;">p63 and 34βE12</span> immunostaining.</span><br clear="none" />
<span style="font-family: 'times new roman', times, serif;">     (with focal aggregates of atypical acini)</span><br clear="none" /></p>
<p><br clear="none" /></p>
<div><br/></div>
</div>
<div><br/></div>
</div>
<div>
<p style="padding-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: 'times new roman', times, serif;"><br clear="none" /></span></p>
</div>
<div><br/></div>
<div><br/></div>
</en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>prostate - benign prostatic tissue</title>
    <created>20171211T064147Z</created>
    <updated>20241202T084254Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>PATHOLOGIC DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Prostate, ___, TRUS-P biopsy --- benign prostatic tissue.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Section shows benign prostatic tissue. No malignancy is observed.</span></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>prostate - benign prostatic tissue (with IHC)</title>
    <created>20161110T145246Z</created>
    <updated>20250512T083518Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.mac</source>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Bilateral specimens show prostatic tissue with focal aggregates of atypical acini.</div><div><br/></div><div>Immunohistochemically, basal cells surrounding the glands are highlighted by p63 and 34βE12 immunostains. No immunoreactivity for AMACR is noted in these atypical acini. These findings indicate a benign process without evidence of malignancy.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><hr/><div>DIAGNOSIS: </div><div>Prostate, ___, TRUS-guided biopsy --- <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Benign prostatic tissue.</span></div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Section shows prostatic tissue with focal aggregates of </span>small acini.</div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Immunohistochemically, basal cells surrounding the glands </span>are highlighted by p63 and 34betaE12 immunostains. No immunoreactivity for AMACR is noted in these acini. These</div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">findings indicate a benign process without evidence of </span>malignancy.</div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Immunohistochemical stains: p63, 34betaE12, AMACR.</span></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Prostate_TURP</title>
    <created>20171228T004713Z</created>
    <updated>20260323T060210Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Prostate, TURP --- Acinar adenocarcinoma (with Gleason sum, ___),</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div>A. Tumor histological type: acinar adenocarcinoma</div><div>B. Tumor histological grade:  </div><div>Primary Gleason pattern: __</div><div>Secondary Gleason pattern: ___</div><div>_ Grade group 1 (Gleason Score 3 + 3 = 6) </div><div>_ Grade group 2 (Gleason Score 3 + 4 = 7) </div><div>_ Grade group 3 (Gleason Score 4 + 3 = 7) </div><div>_ Grade group 4 (Gleason Score 4 + 4 = 8) </div><div>_ Grade group 4 (Gleason Score 3 + 5 = 8) </div><div>_ Grade group 4 (Gleason Score 5 + 3 = 8) </div><div>_ Grade group 5 (Gleason Score 4 + 5 = 9) </div><div>_ Grade group 5 (Gleason Score 5 + 4 = 9) </div><div>_ Grade group 5 (Gleason Score 5 + 5 = 10)</div><div>Reference:</div><div>1.Well differentiation (Gleason sun, 6 or less); moderate (7); poor (8-10)</div><div>2.Simple definitions for Gleason grade:</div><div>Grade 1: Well-circumscribed nodule of adenocarcinoma composed of crowded well-differentiated glands;</div><div>Grade 2: Similar to pattern 1 but with minor infiltration at border;</div><div>Grade 3: Well-formed glands infiltrating benign glands;</div><div>Grade 4: Fused poorly-defined glands, large cribriform glands, hypernephroid pattern;</div><div>Grade 5: Undifferentiated masses or single cells</div><div>C. <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Estimated percentage of prostatic tissue involved by tumor: ____%</span></div><div>D.Lymphovascular invasion: present / absent</div><div>E. Perineural invasion:</div><div>F. Immunohistochemistry: No basal cells surrounding the neoplastic glands are demonstrated by p63 and 34betaE12. The neoplastic glands are positive for <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">AMRCA</span>, confirming the diagnosis.</div><div>Additional findings: Nodular hyperplasia.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Prostatitis</title>
    <created>20230216T130415Z</created>
    <updated>20250515T052456Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Benign prostatic tissue with mild / moderate / severe chronic inflammation (with mild / moderate / severe acute inflammation, with mild / moderate / severe granulomatous inflammation).</div><div><br/></div><div>*Prostatitis is a clinical term only, so it should not be diagnosed on pathology reports</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Renomedullary interstitial cell tumor</title>
    <created>20161208T082113Z</created>
    <updated>20161208T082121Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Section of nodule show spindle cells in a basophilic matrix, admixed with some entrapped renal tubules. The stroma is positive for Alcian blue. These findings suggest a renomedullary interstitial cell tumor (medullary fibroma). </div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
